OL,3,CWater firms across South were
OL,4,Crepeatedly warned by regulator about
OL,5,Csupply risks
OL,7,FHe added: "Three million litres of
OL,8,Fdrinking water are lost every day
OL,9,Fthrough leaking pipes and not a single
OL,10,Fnew major reservoir has been built
OL,11,Fsince privatisation in the late 1980s.
OL,13,F"The public has paid through rising
OL,14,Fbills ` now water companies must
OL,15,Finvest to prevent taps running dry and
OL,16,Fserious damage to the economy, food
OL,17,Fsecurity, industry and our health."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/15
