OL,5,Csupply risks
OL,7,F"However, our water supplies are
OL,8,Fincreasingly at risk because of
OL,9,Ffundamentally flawed official
OL,10,Fforecasts.
OL,12,F"For example, water companies must
OL,13,Fassume people will drastically reduce
OL,14,Ftheir use of water and that businesses
OL,15,Fwill fail to grow.
OL,17,F"That is no way to plan for something
OL,18,Fso precious as water.
